{"id":"TGR-s50.6","title":"xCPS: Implement Noether charge Q","description":"Implement the Noether charge (d-2)-form Q^{μν}[ξ] such that on-shell J^μ = ∇_ν Q^{μν}. For EH gravity:
  Q^{μν} = -∇^{[μ} ξ^{ν]}

The Noether charge is the integrand of conserved charges: H[ξ] = ∫_∂Σ Q. For Killing vectors, this gives Komar integrals. For horizons, this gives black hole entropy.

Requires potential extraction (finding Q from dQ = J). Add to src/phase_space/.

Ground truth: Wald (1990) Eq 2.8; Iyer & Wald, PRD 50, 846 (1994).

Acceptance: noether_charge(J, or equivalently L, field, xi) returns Q^{μν}. Verify for EH: Q = -∇^[μ ξ^ν].","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","owner":"tobias.osborne@itp.uni-hannover.de","created_at":"2026-03-14T22:15:17Z","created_by":"tobiasosborne","updated_at":"2026-03-14T22:15:17Z"}

{"id":"TGR-4zw.1","title":"Research: Design multi-field PSALTer for arbitrary tensor spin projectors","description":"Design how to extend spin_project for vector fields A_μ, antisymmetric B_{μν}, rank-3 fields. Key insight: each field type has different spin content. Vector: spin-1 ⊕ spin-0. Antisymmetric rank-2: spin-1 ⊕ spin-0. Rank-3: depends on symmetry. Document projector algebra for each case. ~100 LOC design doc in notes.

Ground truth: Barker, Marzo, Sherrill (2024), arXiv:2406.09500, Sec 2-3.

Acceptance: Design document specifying projector definitions for vector, antisymmetric-2, and rank-3 fields. API surface for multi-field kernel extraction.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","owner":"tobias.osborne@itp.uni-hannover.de","created_at":"2026-03-14T22:11:30Z","created_by":"tobiasosborne","updated_at":"2026-03-14T22:11:30Z"}

{"id":"TGR-4zw.3","title":"PSALTer: Implement antisymmetric rank-2 field spin projectors","description":"Implement spin projectors for antisymmetric rank-2 field B_{μν} = -B_{νμ}. In d=4, spin content is 1 ⊕ 0. Build projectors from θ_{μν} and ω_{μν} (vector projectors) contracted with antisymmetric structure. Add to src/action/.

Ground truth: PSALTer arXiv:2406.09500, Sec 3.2.

Acceptance: antisym2_spin1_projector and antisym2_spin0_projector functions. Verify completeness and orthogonality on antisymmetric subspace. Verify Kalb-Ramond B-field spectrum.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","owner":"tobias.osborne@itp.uni-hannover.de","created_at":"2026-03-14T22:11:47Z","created_by":"tobiasosborne","updated_at":"2026-03-14T22:11:47Z"}

